<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\07_gilded_vale\07_raed_fampyr</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>20</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you approach the smiling woman at the side of the road, you are struck with a sense of unease. At this distance you can see that her skin has a sickly, pallid sheen to it, and her eyes are the glassy milk-white of a cadaver. Her expression sits oddly on her face, as if it requires great effort to maintain.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I will escort you to him, if you wish."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes. Take me to him." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Attack.] "You'll die with him, monster." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A loyal servant, granted a boon for her good service. Like my lord, I will persist beyond the cycle, and walk an eternity upon the earth. Seek answers from him directly, if you want them." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave] "Not yet. I need some time to prepare." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Come, then. He waits for you there." She points up towards the topmost tower of the keep, and leads the way over the drawbridge.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You have put this off long enough. Will you meet our lord's challenge?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Lord Raedric has been expecting you." The woman smiles a little wider. "It is good that you have not refused his challenge. He feared you might prove a coward, in the end." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then you shall have it. But be warned - you will not escape his vengeance, wherever you should flee." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Lord Raedric waits for you upon the tower."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It is true, then. You have been graced with Berath's favor." The pale creature glances past you. "A great champion of the lord of death." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Greater than he whom I served." After a moment, she drops to one knee. "I would serve you loyally, my lord, if you would have me. What power I hold would be yours to command." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>"Greater than he whom I served." After a moment, she drops to one knee. "I would serve you loyally, my lady, if you would have me. What power I hold would be yours to command." </FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Very well. Go to my stronghold at Caed Nua." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A walking corpse for a servant? I think not." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>The fampyr rises, bowing neatly. "Thank you, my lord. I will travel there at once." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>The fampyr rises, bowing neatly. "Thank you, my lady. I will travel there at once." </FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We will do the Twinned God's work." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You have your victory, champion." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I see." After a few moments, the fampyr rises to her feet. She inclines her head. "Then go with the Twinned God's blessing. I will take my own path." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>